# Azure Functions

## Definition

- Azure Functions is a **serverless compute service** that allows developers to run code without managing servers.
- Code is executed only when triggered by an event.
- Billing is based on execution time and resource consumption.

---

## Why is it used?

- Build event-driven applications.
- Automate background tasks.
- Process files and images.
- Respond to HTTP requests.
- Integrate Azure services.
- Reduce infrastructure management.

---

## Key Features

- Serverless architecture.
- Event-driven execution.
- Automatic scaling.
- Pay-per-execution pricing (Consumption Plan).
- Multiple language support.
- Easy integration with Azure services.
- Supports Durable Functions for workflows.

---

## Advantages

- No server management.
- Automatic scaling.
- Cost-effective.
- Fast deployment.
- Ideal for small tasks and automation.

---

## Disadvantages

- Cold start delay in Consumption Plan.
- Execution time limits in some hosting plans.
- Not suitable for long-running applications without Durable Functions.

---

## Components

### Function App

- Container that hosts one or more Azure Functions.

### Function

- Individual piece of executable code.

### Trigger

- Starts the execution of a function.

### Input Binding

- Reads data from another service automatically.

### Output Binding

- Writes data to another service automatically.

---

## Common Trigger Types

| Trigger | Use Case |
|----------|----------|
| HTTP Trigger | REST APIs and webhooks |
| Timer Trigger | Scheduled jobs |
| Blob Trigger | Process uploaded files |
| Queue Trigger | Process queue messages |
| Event Grid Trigger | React to Azure events |
| Service Bus Trigger | Enterprise messaging |
| Cosmos DB Trigger | React to database changes |

---

## Workflow

```text
Event Occurs
      ↓
Trigger Activated
      ↓
Azure Function Executes
      ↓
Process Data
      ↓
Return Response / Store Output
```

---

## Hosting Plans

| Hosting Plan | Description |
|--------------|-------------|
| Consumption Plan | Pay only when functions execute; automatic scaling |
| Premium Plan | Faster startup, no cold starts, advanced scaling |
| Dedicated (App Service) Plan | Runs on reserved App Service resources |

---

## Real-world Example

Whenever a user uploads an image to Azure Blob Storage, an Azure Function automatically resizes the image and stores the optimized version in another container.

---

## Interview Tip

"Azure Functions is a serverless compute service where code runs only when triggered by an event, eliminating the need to manage servers."

---

## Quick Revision

- Serverless compute service.
- Event-driven execution.
- Automatic scaling.
- Pay-per-execution.
- Uses Triggers and Bindings.
- Supports multiple programming languages.
- Ideal for automation and microservices.

---

